{% if heroImage %}
<div class="home-hero-wrapper">
  <div class="home-slideshow-fs">
    <img src="{{ heroImage }}" alt="{{ title }}" class="img-cover">
  </div>
  <section class="home-hero-overlay">
    <p class="section-label" id="exp-hero-eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Guided Wildlife Walks</p>
    <h1 class="home-title">Wildlife Walks &amp; Photography Workshops in Squamish, BC</h1>
    <p class="home-intro">Squamish, British Columbia</p>
    <div class="scroll-hint">
      <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M7 13l5 5 5-5M7 6l5 5 5-5"/></svg>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
{% endif %}


<div class="standard-page">

  <!-- Toggle -->
  <div class="exp-toggle-wrap">
    <div class="exp-toggle">
      <button class="exp-toggle-btn active" data-mode="walks">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="3"/><line x1="21" y1="21" x2="16.65" y2="16.65"/></svg>
        Guided Walks
      </button>
      <button class="exp-toggle-btn" data-mode="workshops">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M23 19a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H3a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h4l2-3h6l2 3h4a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/><circle cx="12" cy="13" r="4"/></svg>
        Photo Workshops
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Currently In -->
  <p class="section-label">Currently In</p>
  <div class="exp-currently-in">
    <h4 class="exp-currently-in-place">Squamish, British Columbia</h4>
    <p class="exp-currently-in-desc">I'm currently offering guided wildlife watching walks and Photography Workshops in Squamish, British Columbia while living and working in this wonderful mountain-town. This is a magical place where land, lakes, rivers, mountains, forests, and the ocean meet in an explosion of incredible scenery and biodiversity.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ===================== GUIDED WALKS ===================== -->
  <div class="exp-section" id="exp-walks">

    <p class="section-label">Why Walk With Me?</p>
    <div class="exp-why-grid">

      <div class="exp-why-card">
        <div class="exp-why-icon">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0 1 18 0z"/><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h4>Local Expertise</h4>
        <p>The Skwelwil'em Squamish Estuary is one of BC's most important wildlife areas, supporting over 200 bird species, salmon, black bear, and species at risk. Spending many hours each week exploring this area has given me intimate knowledge of this connected estuarine ecosystem, I know where to look and when.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="exp-why-card">
        <div class="exp-why-icon">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h4>Ethical Observation</h4>
        <p>Every nature walk is led with a non-intrusive, wildlife-first approach. We move slowly, observe carefully, and leave the area just as it was when we arrived.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="exp-why-card">
        <div class="exp-why-icon">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-7.78z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h4>Free &amp; Informal</h4>
        <p>These are relaxed, free of charge guided bird walks for anyone who wants to explore. I'm grateful to be able to explore this wonderful area, and I love little more than sharing it with others. So whether you're a seasoned birder or have never held a pair of binoculars, come join a walk when you're here in Squamish.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <p class="section-label" style="margin-top: 3rem;">What To Expect</p>
    <div class="exp-format-grid">

      <div class="exp-format-card">
        <div class="exp-format-header">
          <div class="exp-format-icon">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="exp-format-label">The Walk</p>
            <h3 class="exp-format-title">2-5 Hours</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="exp-format-desc">We'll walk the Squamish estuary at a slow, deliberate pace, with lots of pausing to watch, listen, and identify what is around us. I'll share what I know about the birds, the landscape, the seasons, and how this incredible system is connected.</p>
        <ul class="exp-format-list">
          <li>Flexible timing: dawn light or golden hour evenings</li>
          <li>Bird and wildlife identification throughout</li>
          <li>Insights into behaviour and ecology of Squamish's wildlife</li>
          <li>Completely free, no booking required. Just get in touch</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="exp-format-card">

        <div class="exp-format-header">
          <div class="exp-format-icon">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="exp-format-label">The Season</p>
            <h3 class="exp-format-title">Year Round</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="exp-format-desc">Squamish has lots to offer regardless of the season. In winter, hundreds of bald eagles gather to feed on spawning salmon, and in spring, tens of thousands of migratory birds arrive.</p>
        <ul class="exp-format-list">
          <li>Peak bald eagle watching Nov–Jan</li>
          <li>Wintering waterfowl and shorebirds</li>
          <li>Migrating warblers and hummingbirds</li>
          <li>Guided walks in Squamish available year-round</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

